  "prompt": "How do I know who is following me on Snapchat?",
  "response": "To see who is following you on Snapchat, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open Snapchat**: Launch the app on your device.\n\n2. **Go to your Profile**: Tap on your **Bitmoji** or **profile icon** in the top-left corner of the camera screen.\n\n3. **View Your Friends List**: Under the \"My Friends\" section, you'll see a list of people who have added you back. This list represents your mutual friends (people you have added and who have added you back).\n\n4. **Check Your Followers (Not Mutual Friends)**:\n   - If someone has added you but you haven\u2019t added them back, they won\u2019t appear in your \"My Friends\" list. Instead, they\u2019ll only appear in your \"Followers\" list.\n   - To see your followers, tap on **Add Friends** (the ghost icon in the top-right corner of the camera screen or the bottom of the profile screen) and then select **Added Me**. This will show a list of people who have added you but you haven\u2019t added back yet.\n\n   Note: Snapchat doesn\u2019t directly label this list as \"Followers,\" but it essentially serves the same purpose.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- You can only see who has added you if you haven\u2019t added them back. Mutual friends (people you\u2019ve added and who\u2019ve added you back) will appear in your friends list.\n- Snapchat\u2019s privacy settings allow you to control who can add you or send you snaps. You can adjust these settings in the app under **Settings** > **Privacy**.\n- If someone has removed you or blocked you, they won\u2019t appear in your friends or followers list.\n\nLet me know if you need further clarification! \ud83d\ude0a",
